## Output Expected
the output of `WithoutDataProviderTest` is correct, but the other outputs should be something along the lines of:
```bash
$./vendor/bin/phpunit tests/Javascript/WithDataProviderTest.php
	Found 2 tests on TestSuite
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithDataProviderTest::testWith    ("foo")
 	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithDataProviderTest::testWith    ("bar")

$ ./vendor/bin/phpunit tests/Javascript/WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest.php
	Found 3 tests on TestSuite
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest::testWith    ("foo")
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest::testWith    ("foo")
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest::testWithout

$ ./vendor/bin/phpunit
	Found 6 tests on TestSuite
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest::testWith    ("foo")
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest::testWith    ("foo")
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithAndWithoutDataProviderTest::testWithout
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithDataProviderTest::testWith    ("foo")
 	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithDataProviderTest::testWith    ("bar")
	- App\Tests\Javascript\WithoutDataProviderTest::testWithout
```
The test count in the `Found N tests` is accurate, but the `tests()` property does not match.
